<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The business activities of the Company are carried out by our employees under the direction and supervision of our President and Chief Executive Officer
(&#147;CEO&#148;). The Board is responsible for overseeing these activities. In doing so, each director is required to use his or her business judgment in the best interests of the Company. The Board&#146;s responsibilities include: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Reviewing the Company&#146;s performance, strategies and major decisions; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Overseeing the Company&#146;s compliance with legal and regulatory requirements and the integrity of its financial statements; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Overseeing the Company&#146;s policies and practices for identifying, managing and mitigating key enterprise risks; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Overseeing management, including reviewing the CEO&#146;s performance and succession planning for key management roles; and </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Overseeing executive and director compensation, and our compensation program and policies. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>Corporate
Governance Guidelines </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Board has adopted Corporate Governance Guidelines that, along with the charters of the Board committees, provide the basic
framework for the Board&#146;s operation and role in the governance of the Company. The guidelines include the Board&#146;s policies regarding director independence, qualifications and responsibilities, access to management and outside advisors,
compensation, continuing education, oversight of management succession and stockholding requirements. They also provide a process for directors to annually evaluate the performance of the Board. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Governance Committee is responsible for overseeing and reviewing the Board&#146;s Corporate Governance Guidelines at least annually and recommending any
proposed changes to the Board for approval. The Corporate Governance Guidelines are available on the Investors section of our website at <I>www.thehersheycompany.com.</I> </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>Code of Ethical Business Conduct </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Board has adopted a
Code of Ethical Business Conduct (the &#147;Code of Conduct&#148;) that applies to all of our directors, officers and employees worldwide. Adherence to this Code of Conduct assures that our directors, officers and employees are held to the highest
standards of integrity. The Code of Conduct covers areas such as conflicts of interest, insider trading and compliance with laws and regulations. The Audit Committee oversees the Company&#146;s communication of, and compliance with, the Code of
Conduct. The Code of Conduct, including amendments thereto or waivers granted to a director or officer, if any, can be viewed on the Investors section of our website at <I>www.thehersheycompany.com.</I> </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">11 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>Stockholder and Interested Party Communications with Directors </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Stockholders and other interested parties may communicate with our directors in several ways. Communications regarding accounting, internal accounting controls
or auditing matters may be emailed to the Audit Committee at auditcommittee@hersheys.com or addressed to the Audit Committee at the following address: </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:8%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Audit Committee </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:8%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">c/o Corporate
Secretary </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:8%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Hershey Company </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:8%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">100 Crystal A Drive </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:8%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">P.O. Box 810
</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:8%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Hershey, PA 17033-0810 </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Stockholders and
other interested parties also can submit comments, confidentially and anonymously if desired, to the Audit Committee by calling the Hershey Concern Line at <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">(800)&nbsp;362-8321</FONT> or by accessing the Hershey
Concern Line website at <I>www.HersheysConcern.com</I>. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Stockholders and other interested parties may contact any of the independent directors, including
the Lead Independent Director, as well as the independent directors as a group, by writing to the specified party at the address set forth above or by emailing the independent directors (or a specific independent director, including the Lead
Independent Director) at independentdirectors@hersheys.com. Stockholders and other interested parties may also contact any of the independent directors using the Hershey Concern Line telephone number or website noted above. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Communications to the Audit Committee, any of the independent directors and the Hershey Concern Line are processed by the Office of General Counsel. The Office
of General Counsel reviews and summarizes these communications and provides reports to the applicable party on a periodic basis. Communications regarding any accounting, internal control or auditing matter are reported immediately to the Audit
Committee, as are allegations about our officers. The Audit Committee will address communications from any interested party in accordance with our Board-approved Procedures for Submission and Handling of Complaints Regarding Compliance Matters,
which are available for viewing on the Investors section of our website at <I>www.thehersheycompany.com</I>. Solicitations, junk mail and obviously frivolous or inappropriate communications are not forwarded to the Audit Committee or the independent
directors, but copies are retained and made available to any director who wishes to review them. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>Director Independence </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Board, in consultation with the Governance Committee, determines which of our directors are independent. The Board has adopted categorical standards for
independence that the Board uses in determining which directors are independent. The Board bases its determination of independence for each director on the more stringent independence standards applicable to Audit Committee members regardless of
whether such director serves on the Audit Committee. These standards are contained in the Board&#146;s Corporate Governance Guidelines. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Applying these
categorical standards for independence, as well as the independence requirements set forth in the listing standards of the New York Stock Exchange (the &#147;NYSE Rules&#148;) and the rules and regulations of the Securities and Exchange Commission
(&#147;SEC&#148;), the Board determined that the following directors recommended for election at the Annual Meeting are independent: Pamela&nbsp;M.&nbsp;Arway, James W. Brown, Charles&nbsp;A.&nbsp;Davis, Mary&nbsp;Kay&nbsp;Haben, M. Diane Koken,
Robert&nbsp;M.&nbsp;Malcolm, James M. Mead, Anthony&nbsp;J.&nbsp;Palmer, Thomas&nbsp;J.&nbsp;Ridge and David&nbsp;L.&nbsp;Shedlarz. The Board determined that John P.&nbsp;Bilbrey is not independent because he served as an executive officer of the
Company until March&nbsp;1, 2017, and that Michele G. Buck is not independent because she is an executive officer of the Company. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">12 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">In making its independence determinations, the Board, in consultation with the Governance Committee, reviewed the
direct and indirect relationships between each director and the Company and its subsidiaries, as well as the compensation and other payments each director received from or made to the Company and its subsidiaries. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">In making its independence determinations with respect to Ms.&nbsp;Koken and Messrs. Brown and Mead, the Board considered their roles as current members of the
board of directors of Hershey Trust Company and the board of managers (governing body) of Milton Hershey School, as well as certain transactions the Company had or may have with these entities. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Hershey Trust Company, as trustee for the trust established by Milton S. and Catherine S. Hershey that has as its sole beneficiary Milton Hershey School (such
trust, the &#147;Milton Hershey School Trust&#148;), is our controlling stockholder. Hershey Trust Company is in turn owned by the Milton Hershey School Trust. As such, Hershey Trust Company, Milton Hershey School, the Milton Hershey School Trust
and companies owned by the Milton Hershey School Trust are considered affiliates of the Company under SEC rules. During 2016, we had a number of transactions with Hershey Trust Company, Milton Hershey School and companies owned by the Milton Hershey
School Trust involving the purchase and sale of goods and services in the ordinary course of business and the leasing of real estate at market rates. We have outlined these transactions in greater detail in the section entitled &#147;Certain
Transactions and Relationships.&#148; We have provided information about Company stock owned by Hershey Trust Company, as trustee for the Milton Hershey School Trust, and by Hershey Trust Company for its own investment purposes in the section
entitled &#147;Information Regarding Our Controlling Stockholder.&#148; </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Ms.&nbsp;Koken and Messrs. Brown and Mead do not receive any compensation from The
Hershey Company, from Hershey Trust Company or from Milton Hershey School other than compensation they receive or will receive in the ordinary course as members of the board of directors or board of managers of each of those entities, as applicable.
In addition, Ms.&nbsp;Koken and Messrs. Brown and Mead do not participate in Board decisions in connection with the Company&#146;s transactions with Hershey Trust Company, Milton Hershey School and companies owned by the Milton Hershey School Trust.
The Board therefore concluded that the positions Ms.&nbsp;Koken and Messrs. Brown and Mead have as members of the board of directors of Hershey Trust Company and the board of managers of Milton Hershey School do not impact their independence. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>Director Nominations </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Governance Committee is
responsible for identifying and recommending to the Board candidates for Board membership. As our controlling stockholder, Hershey Trust Company, as trustee for the Milton Hershey School Trust, also may from time to time recommend to the Governance
Committee, or elect outright, individuals to serve on our Board. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">In administering its responsibilities, the Governance Committee has not adopted formal
selection procedures, but instead utilizes general guidelines that allow it to adjust the selection process to best satisfy the objectives established for any director search. The Governance Committee considers director candidates recommended by any
reasonable source, including current directors, management, stockholders (including Hershey Trust Company, as trustee for the Milton Hershey School Trust) and other sources. The Governance Committee evaluates all director candidates in the same
manner, regardless of the source of the recommendation. The Governance Committee has established a policy that it will not recommend a candidate to the full Board until all members of the Governance Committee have interviewed and approved the
candidate for nomination. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">13 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Occasionally, the Governance Committee engages a paid third-party consultant to assist in identifying and
evaluating director candidates. The Governance Committee has sole authority under its charter to retain, compensate and terminate these consultants. In 2016, the Governance Committee retained Egon Zehnder to assist in identifying potential future
director candidates as several current directors approach their 72<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">nd</SUP> birthday. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Stockholders desiring
to recommend or nominate a director candidate must comply with certain procedures. If you are a stockholder and desire to nominate a director candidate at the 2018 Annual Meeting of Stockholders of the Company, you must comply with the procedures
for nomination set forth in the section entitled &#147;Information Regarding the 2018 Annual Meeting of Stockholders.&#148; Stockholders who do not intend to nominate a director at an annual meeting may recommend a director candidate to the
Governance Committee for consideration at any time. Stockholders desiring to do so must submit their recommendation in writing to The Hershey Company, c/o Corporate Secretary, 100 Crystal A Drive, Hershey, Pennsylvania 17033-0810, and include in the
submission all of the information that would be required if the stockholder nominated the candidate at an annual meeting. The Governance Committee may require the nominating stockholder to submit additional information before considering the
candidate. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">There were no changes to the procedures relating to stockholder nominations during 2016, and there have been no changes to such procedures to
date in 2017. These procedural requirements are intended to ensure the Governance Committee has sufficient time and a basis on which to assess potential director candidates and are not intended to discourage or interfere with appropriate stockholder
nominations. The Governance Committee does not believe that these procedural requirements subject any stockholder or proposed nominee to unreasonable burdens. The Governance Committee and the Board reserve the right to change the procedural
requirements from time to time and/or to waive some or all of the requirements with respect to certain nominees, but any such waiver shall not preclude the Governance Committee from insisting upon compliance with any and all of the above
requirements by any other recommending stockholder or proposed nominees. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><B><A NAME="toc348571_11"></A>THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>General Oversight </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Board has general oversight
responsibility for the Company&#146;s affairs. Although the Board does not have responsibility for <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">day-to-day</FONT></FONT> management of the Company, Board members stay informed
about the Company&#146;s business through regular meetings, site visits and other periodic interactions with management. The Board is deeply involved in the Company&#146;s strategic planning process. The Board also plays an important oversight role
in the Company&#146;s leadership development and succession planning processes. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>Composition </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Board is currently comprised of 12 members, each serving a <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">one-year</FONT> term that expires at the Annual Meeting. Ten of
the 12 director nominees are considered independent under the NYSE Rules and the Board&#146;s Corporate Governance Guidelines. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">14 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>Leadership Structure </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Company&#146;s governance documents provide the Board with flexibility to select the leadership structure that is most appropriate for the Company and its
stockholders. The Board regularly evaluates its governance structure and has concluded that the Company and its stockholders are best served by not having a formal policy regarding whether the same individual should serve as both Chairman of the
Board and CEO. This approach allows the Board to exercise its business judgment in determining the most appropriate leadership structure in light of the current facts and circumstances facing the Company, including the composition and tenure of the
Board, the tenure of the CEO, the strength of the Company&#146;s management team, the Company&#146;s recent financial performance, the Company&#146;s current strategic plan and the current economic environment, among other factors. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Throughout 2016, John P. Bilbrey served as our Chairman of the Board and CEO. The Board believed that combining the roles of Chairman of the Board and CEO
under Mr.&nbsp;Bilbrey&#146;s leadership was in the best interests of the Company and its stockholders for several reasons: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Mr.&nbsp;Bilbrey&#146;s strong working relationship and high level of trust with the Board, gained through more than six years of service as a director; </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Mr.&nbsp;Bilbrey&#146;s deep understanding of Board governance and operations, the result of having worked with the prior Chairman of the Board and current Lead Independent Director to develop meeting topics, set
meeting schedules and agendas, and ensure efficient communications among the directors; and </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Mr.&nbsp;Bilbrey&#146;s unparalleled knowledge of the Company and its products, which the Board believed put him in the best position to lead the Board through the strategic business issues facing the Company.
</TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Effective March&nbsp;1, 2017, the Board split the roles of Chairman of the Board and CEO, with Michele&nbsp;G.&nbsp;Buck assuming
responsibility as President and CEO and Mr.&nbsp;Bilbrey transitioning to the role of <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Non-Executive</FONT> Chairman of the Board. The Board believes this leadership structure is the most appropriate at this time as
it enables the Company to continue to leverage Mr.&nbsp;Bilbrey&#146;s knowledge of the Company and his expertise in Board governance and operations while allowing Ms.&nbsp;Buck to focus on her new responsibilities as CEO. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Board also recognizes the importance of strong independent Board leadership. Although no longer serving as an executive officer of the Company, the Board
has determined that Mr.&nbsp;Bilbrey is not independent at this time due to his prior service as CEO. For that reason, James E. Nevels continues to serve as Lead Independent Director, a position he has held since April&nbsp;2, 2015. Having
previously served as Chairman of the Board from February 2009 until his appointment as Lead Independent Director, Mr.&nbsp;Nevels&#146;s service helps ensure continuity of independent Board leadership as well as effective communication between the
CEO, the Chairman of the Board, and the independent directors. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Under the terms of the Board&#146;s Corporate Governance Guidelines, the Lead Independent
Director&#146;s responsibilities include the following: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">In the absence of the Chairman of the Board, presiding at all Board and stockholder meetings; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Calling meetings of the independent directors of the Board, in addition to the executive sessions of independent directors held during each Board meeting; </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Establishing the agenda and presiding at all executive sessions and other meetings of the independent directors of the Board; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Communicating with the independent directors of the Board between meetings as necessary or appropriate; </TD></TR></TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">15 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">


<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Serving as a liaison between the Chairman of the Board and the independent directors, ensuring independent director consensus is communicated to the Chairman of the Board, and communicating the results of meetings of
the independent directors to the Chairman of the Board and members of management, as appropriate; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Approving Board meeting agendas and schedules to assure there is sufficient time for discussion of all agenda items; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Approving Board meeting materials and other information sent to the Board; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Evaluating the quality and timeliness of information sent to the Board by the CEO and other members of management; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Assisting the Chairman of the Board on matters of Board succession planning and crisis management; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Overseeing the evaluation of the CEO; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Assisting the chair of the Governance Committee with Board and individual director evaluations; and </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Being available for consultation and direct communication at the request of major stockholders. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Board has
determined that Mr.&nbsp;Nevels is an independent member of the Board under the NYSE Rules and the Board&#146;s Corporate Governance Guidelines. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Mr.&nbsp;Nevels is not standing for <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">re-election</FONT> as a director at the Annual Meeting. Pursuant to the terms of the
Board&#146;s Corporate Governance Guidelines, the independent directors are currently considering potential candidates from among the other independent members of the Board to replace Mr.&nbsp;Nevels as Lead Independent Director upon expiration of
his term. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">In addition to the Lead Independent Director role, the Board has established five standing committees to assist with its oversight
responsibilities: (1)&nbsp;Audit Committee; (2)&nbsp;Compensation and Executive Organization Committee (&#147;Compensation Committee&#148;); (3)&nbsp;Finance and Risk Management Committee; (4)&nbsp;Governance Committee; and (5)&nbsp;Executive
Committee. Each of the Audit Committee, the Compensation Committee, the Finance and Risk Management Committee, and the Governance Committee is comprised entirely of independent directors. Finally, Mr.&nbsp;Mead is a direct representative of the
Company&#146;s largest stockholder. This composition of our Board helps to ensure that boardroom discussions reflect the views of management, our independent directors and our stockholders. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>Board Role in Risk Oversight </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Our Board takes an active
role in risk oversight. While management is responsible for identifying, evaluating, managing and mitigating the Company&#146;s exposure to risk, it is the Board&#146;s responsibility to oversee the Company&#146;s risk management process and to
ensure that management is taking appropriate action to identify, manage and mitigate key risks. The Board administers its risk oversight responsibilities both through active review and discussion of key risks facing the Company and by delegating
certain risk oversight responsibilities to committees for further consideration and evaluation. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">In August 2009, the Board established the Finance and Risk
Management Committee. This committee was established, in part, to enhance the Board&#146;s oversight of how senior management manages the material risks facing the Company. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">16 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The following table summarizes the role of the Board and each of its committees in overseeing risk: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">


<TR>
<TD WIDTH="27%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="3%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="69%"></TD></TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#3f000b" STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-TOP:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #999999; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><FONT
 COLOR="#ffffff"><B><FONT COLOR="#ffffff">Governing&nbsp;Body</FONT></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt" align="left">&nbsp;</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #999999; BORDER-TOP:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #999999">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #999999; padding-right:2pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><FONT
 COLOR="#ffffff"><B><FONT COLOR="#ffffff">Role&nbsp;in&nbsp;Risk&nbsp;Oversight</FONT></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt" align="left">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>


<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #3f000b; padding-left:8pt">Board</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #3f000b; padding-right:2pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Regularly
reviews and evaluates the Company&#146;s strategic plans and associated risks.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Oversees the Company&#146;s enterprise risk management (&#147;ERM&#148;) framework and the
overall ERM process.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Conducts annual succession plan reviews to ensure the Company maintains appropriate succession
plans for members of senior management.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #3f000b; padding-left:8pt" BGCOLOR="#bfbfbf">Audit Committee</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#bfbfbf" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #3f000b; padding-right:2pt" BGCOLOR="#bfbfbf">
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Oversees compliance with legal and regulatory requirements and the Company&#146;s Code of
Conduct.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Oversees
risks relating to key accounting policies.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Reviews internal controls with the Principal Financial Officer, Principal Accounting Officer
and internal auditors.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Meets regularly with representatives of the Company&#146;s independent auditors.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:2pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #3f000b; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">Compensation and</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">Executive Organization</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">Committee</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #3f000b; padding-right:2pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Oversees risks
relating to the Company&#146;s compensation program and policies.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Oversees the process for conducting annual risk assessments of the Company&#146;s compensation
policies and practices.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Employs independent compensation consultants to assist in reviewing the Company&#146;s
compensation program, including the potential risks created by such program.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Oversees the Company&#146;s succession planning and talent processes and programs.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:2pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #3f000b; padding-left:8pt" BGCOLOR="#bfbfbf"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">Finance and Risk</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">Management Committee</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#bfbfbf" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #3f000b; padding-right:2pt" BGCOLOR="#bfbfbf">
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Reviews enterprise-level and other key risks identified through the Company&#146;s ERM process
as well as management&#146;s plans to mitigate those risks.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Oversees key financial risks.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Oversees and approves
proposed merger and acquisition activities and related risks.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Chair meets at least annually with the Audit Committee to discuss the Company&#146;s risk
management programs.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #3f000b; padding-left:8pt">Governance Committee</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #3f000b; padding-right:2pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Oversees risks
relating to the Company&#146;s governance structure and other corporate governance matters and processes.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Oversees compliance with key corporate governance documents, including the Corporate
Governance Guidelines and the Insider Trading Policy.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b; padding-left:8pt" BGCOLOR="#bfbfbf">Executive Committee</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#bfbfbf" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b; padding-right:2pt" BGCOLOR="#bfbfbf">
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Reviews and approves, through a special committee of independent directors on the Executive
Committee, any related party transactions between the Company and entities affiliated with the Company and certain of its directors.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
</TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">17 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The decision to administer the Board&#146;s oversight responsibilities in this manner has an important effect on
the Board&#146;s leadership and committee structure, described in more detail above. The Board believes that its structure &#150; including a strong Lead Independent Director, 10 of 12 independent directors and key committees comprised entirely of
independent directors &#150; helps to ensure that key strategic decisions made by senior management, up to and including the CEO, are reviewed and overseen by independent directors of the Board. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>Experiences, Skills and Qualifications </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Governance
Committee works with the Board to determine the appropriate characteristics, skills and experiences that should be possessed by the Board as a whole as well as its individual members. While the Governance Committee has not established minimum
criteria for director candidates, in general, the Board seeks individuals with skills and backgrounds that will complement those of other directors and maximize the diversity and effectiveness of the Board as a whole. The Board also seeks
individuals who bring unique and varied perspectives and life experiences to the Board. As such, the Governance Committee assists the Board by recommending prospective director candidates who will enhance the overall diversity of the Board. The
Board views diversity broadly, taking into consideration the age, professional experience, race, education, gender and other attributes of its members. In addition, the Board&#146;s Corporate Governance Guidelines describe the general experiences,
qualifications, attributes and skills sought by the Board of any director nominee, including: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:9pt" ALIGN="center">

the experiences of the other Board members</P></TD>

products</P></TD></TR>

Overall desirability as an addition to the Board and its committees</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b; padding-right:2pt">
<P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.33em; text-indent:-1.33em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#10003; &nbsp;Government, public policy and regulatory affairs</P></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">In addition to evaluating new director candidates, the Governance Committee regularly assesses the composition of the Board in
order to ensure it reflects an appropriate balance of knowledge, skills, expertise, diversity and independence. As part of this assessment, each director is asked to identify and assess the particular experiences, skills and other attributes that
qualify him or her to serve as a member of the Board. Based on the most recent assessment of the Board&#146;s composition completed in February 2017, the Governance Committee and the Board have determined that, in light of the Company&#146;s current
business structure and strategies, the Board has an appropriate mix of director experiences, skills, qualifications and backgrounds. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">A description of the
most relevant experiences, skills, attributes and qualifications that qualify each director nominee to serve as a member of the Board is included in his or her biography. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">18 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><B><A NAME="toc348571_12"></A>MEETINGS AND COMMITTEES OF THE BOARD </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>Meetings of the Board of Directors and Director Attendance at Annual Meeting </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Board held 13 meetings in 2016. Each director attended at least 83% of all of the meetings of the Board and committees of the Board on which he or she
served in 2016. Average attendance for all of these meetings equaled 94%. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">In addition, the independent directors meet regularly in executive session at
every Board meeting and at other times as the independent directors deem necessary. These meetings allow the independent directors to discuss important issues, including the business and affairs of the Company as well as matters concerning
management, without any member of management present. Each executive session is chaired by the Lead Independent Director. In the absence of the Lead Independent Director, executive sessions are chaired by an independent director assigned on a
rotating basis. Members of the Audit Committee, Compensation Committee, Finance and Risk Management Committee, and Governance Committee also meet regularly in executive session. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Directors are expected to attend our annual meetings of stockholders. Ten of the eleven directors standing for election at the 2016 Annual Meeting of
Stockholders of the Company attended that meeting. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>Committees of the Board </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Board has established five standing committees. Membership on each of these committees, as of March&nbsp;6, 2017, is shown in the following chart: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Ex-Officio </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">All directors, including committee chairs, served on the respective committees listed above
throughout 2016. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Board&#146;s Corporate Governance Guidelines require that every member of the Audit Committee, Compensation Committee, Finance and
Risk Management Committee, and Governance Committee be independent. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">19 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Board may also from time to time establish committees of limited duration for a special purpose. In 2016,
the&nbsp;Board established a special committee to oversee the Company&#146;s CEO search process. This special committee was chaired by Ms.&nbsp;Arway and included Ms.&nbsp;Haben and Messrs. Malcolm, Mead, Nevels and Shedlarz as members. The special
committee met four times in 2016. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The table below identifies the number of meetings held by each standing committee in 2016, provides a brief description
of the duties and responsibilities of each committee, and provides general information regarding the location of each committee&#146;s charter: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:9pt" ALIGN="center">

<P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:0.67em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff"><B>Committee</B></FONT></P></TD>

<P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><B>Audit</B></FONT></P></TD></TR>

<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:9pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #999999" BGCOLOR="#3f000b"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:0.67em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff"><B>Duties and
Responsibilities</B></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;</TD>

<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.56em; text-indent:-1.11em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Oversee the Company&#146;s financial reporting processes and the integrity of the
Company&#146;s financial statements.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.56em; text-indent:-1.11em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Oversee the Company&#146;s compliance with legal and regulatory requirements.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.56em; text-indent:-1.11em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Oversee the performance of
the Company&#146;s independent auditors and the internal audit function.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.56em; text-indent:-1.11em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Approve all audit and <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-audit</FONT> services and fees.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.56em; text-indent:-1.11em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Oversee (in consultation
with the Finance and Risk Management Committee) the Company&#146;s risk management processes and policies.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.56em; text-indent:-1.11em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Review the adequacy of internal controls.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.56em; text-indent:-1.11em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Review and discuss with
management Quarterly Reports on Form <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">10-Q</FONT> and Annual Report on <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Form&nbsp;10-K</FONT> prior to filing with the SEC.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.56em; text-indent:-1.11em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Review and discuss with
management earnings releases.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:1.56em; text-indent:-1.11em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Administer the Company&#146;s Procedures for Submission and Handling of Complaints Regarding
Compliance Matters.</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:9pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b" BGCOLOR="#3f000b"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:0.67em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff"><B>General

<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.56em; text-indent:-1.11em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The Board has determined that all directors on the Audit Committee are financially literate.
The Board has also determined that Messrs. Davis, Mead and Nevels qualify as&nbsp;&#147;audit committee financial experts&#148; as defined in SEC regulations and that each has accounting or related financial management expertise.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.56em; text-indent:-1.11em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Charter can be viewed on
the Investors section of our website at<I>&nbsp;www.thehersheycompany.com.</I></P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:1.56em; text-indent:-1.11em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Charter prohibits any member of the Audit Committee from serving on the audit committees of
more than two other public companies unless the Board determines that such simultaneous service would not impair the ability of the director to effectively serve&nbsp;on the Committee.</P></TD></TR></TABLE>

the Board regarding CEO compensation.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.56em; text-indent:-1.11em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Review and recommend to the Board the form and amount of director compensation.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.56em; text-indent:-1.11em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Make equity grants under
and administer the Company&#146;s Equity and Incentive Compensation Plan (the &#147;EICP&#148;).</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.56em; text-indent:-1.11em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Establish target award levels and make awards under the annual cash incentive component of the
EICP.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.56em; text-indent:-1.11em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Monitor
executive compensation arrangements for consistency with corporate objectives and stockholders&#146; interests.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.56em; text-indent:-1.11em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Review the executive organization of the Company.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.56em; text-indent:-1.11em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Monitor the development of
personnel available to fill key executive positions as part of the succession planning process.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>

<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.56em; text-indent:-1.11em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Identify, evaluate and

<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.56em; text-indent:-1.11em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Review and make recommendations to the Board on corporate governance matters and policies,
including the Board&#146;s Corporate Governance Guidelines.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.56em; text-indent:-1.11em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Administer the Company&#146;s Related Person Transaction Policy as directed by the Board.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:1.56em; text-indent:-1.11em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Evaluate the performance
of the Board, its independent committees and each director.</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:9pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b" BGCOLOR="#3f000b"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:0.67em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff"><B>General
Information</B></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b; padding-right:2pt">
<P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.56em; text-indent:-1.11em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Charter can be viewed on the Investors section of our website
at<I>&nbsp;www.thehersheycompany.com.</I></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;</TD>

<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:9pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #999999" BGCOLOR="#3f000b"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:0.67em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff"><B>Meetings</B></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b; padding-right:2pt">1</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:9pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #999999" BGCOLOR="#3f000b"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:0.67em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff"><B>Duties and
Responsibilities</B></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b; padding-right:2pt">
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.56em; text-indent:-1.11em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Manage the business and affairs of the Company, to the extent permitted by the Delaware General
Corporation Law, when the Board is not in session.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.56em; text-indent:-1.11em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Review and approve, through a subcommittee consisting of the independent directors on the
Executive Committee who are not affiliated with Hershey Trust Company, Hershey Entertainment&nbsp;&amp; Resorts Company and/or Milton Hershey School, or any of their affiliates, any transaction not in the ordinary course of business between the
Company and any of these entities, unless otherwise provided by the Board or the Corporate Governance Guidelines.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:1.56em; text-indent:-1.11em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Currently, the Corporate Governance Guidelines provide that, unless directed otherwise by the
independent members of the Board who have no affiliation with any of the above entities, such transactions will be reviewed and approved in advance by a special committee consisting of the directors elected by the holders of our Common Stock voting
separately, and only in the absence of such directors will the subcommittee of the Executive Committee approve such transactions.</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:9pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b" BGCOLOR="#3f000b"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:0.67em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff"><B>General
Information</B></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;</TD>

at<I>&nbsp;www.thehersheycompany.com.</I></P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

transactions, please refer to the section entitled &#147;Certain Transactions and Relationships.&#148;</P></TD></TR>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:13.5pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><B><A NAME="toc348571_13"></A>PROPOSAL NO. 1 &#150; ELECTION OF DIRECTORS
</B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:40pt" ALIGN="center">


<TR>
<TD></TD>
<TD></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="4%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="90%"></TD></TR>


<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:12pt">
<TD VALIGN="middle" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-TOP:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b; padding-left:8pt"><FONT STYLE="font-size:40pt">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b" ALIGN="right"><FONT STYLE="font-size:40pt">&#10003;</FONT></TD>
<TD NOWRAP VALIGN="middle" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b"><FONT STYLE="font-size:40pt">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#3f000b" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b; padding-right:2pt" BGCOLOR="#3f000b">
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff">The Board of Directors unanimously recommends that stockholders<BR>vote
<B>FOR</B> each of the nominees for director at the<BR>2017 Annual Meeting</FONT></P></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The first proposal to be voted on at the Annual Meeting is the election of 12 directors. If elected, the directors will hold
office until the 2018 Annual Meeting of Stockholders of the Company or until their successors are elected and qualified. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>Election Procedures </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">We have two classes of common stock outstanding: Common Stock and Class&nbsp;B Common Stock. Under our certificate of incorporation and <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">by-laws:</FONT> </P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="1%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">One-sixth</FONT> of the total number of our directors (which equates presently to two directors) will be elected by the holders of our Common Stock voting separately as a class. For the
2017 Annual Meeting, the Board has nominated Mary Kay Haben and Robert M. Malcolm for election by the holders of our Common Stock voting separately as a class. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="1%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">The remaining 10 directors will be elected by the holders of our Common Stock and Class&nbsp;B Common Stock voting together without regard to class. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">With respect to the nominees to be elected by the holders of the Common Stock and the Class&nbsp;B Common Stock voting together, the nine nominees receiving
the greatest number of votes of the Common Stock and Class&nbsp;B Common Stock will be elected as directors. With respect to the nominees to be elected by the holders of the Common Stock voting separately as a class, the two nominees receiving the
greatest number of votes of the Common Stock will be elected as directors. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Board&#146;s Corporate Governance Guidelines provide that directors will
generally not be nominated for <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">re-election</FONT> after their 72<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">nd</SUP> birthday. All of the directors standing for election at the 2017 Annual Meeting satisfied the
applicable age requirement at the time of their nomination. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">All nominees for election as director have indicated their willingness to serve if elected. If
a nominee becomes unavailable for election for any reason, the proxies will have discretionary authority to vote for a substitute. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>Nominees for
Director </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Board unanimously recommends the following nominees for election at the 2017 Annual Meeting. These nominees were recommended to the Board
by the Governance Committee. In making its recommendation, the Governance Committee considered the experience, qualifications, attributes and skills of each nominee, as well as each director&#146;s past performance on our Board, as reflected in the
Governance Committee&#146;s annual evaluation of Board and committee performance. This evaluation considers, among other things, each director&#146;s individual contributions to the Board, the director&#146;s ability to work collaboratively with
other directors and the effectiveness of the Board as a whole. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Mr.&nbsp;Nevels, the current Lead Independent Director, and Mr.&nbsp;Cavanaugh are not
standing for <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">re-election</FONT> at the Annual Meeting. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">On the following pages, we provide certain biographical
information about each nominee for director, as well as information regarding the nominee&#146;s specific experience, qualifications, attributes and skills that qualify him or her to serve as a director and as a member of the committee(s) of the
Board on which the nominee serves. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">22 </P>

<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;Executive (Chair)</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" COLSPAN="3"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10.5pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><B><I>JOHN P. BILBREY</I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:7.5pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>Chairman of the Board, The Hershey Company (March 2017 to present)</B></P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:7.5pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><B><I>QUALIFICATIONS, ATTRIBUTES AND SKILLS</I></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Having served as our President and Chief Executive Officer from May 2011 to March 2017, Mr.&nbsp;Bilbrey has a thorough and comprehensive knowledge of all
aspects of the Company&#146;s business. He has extensive experience in the consumer packaged goods and fast-moving consumer goods categories in the United States and international markets and has the benefit of having served as both Chief Executive
Officer and Chief Operating Officer of the Company. His leadership within the Company, as well as his extensive industry and international experience, make Mr.&nbsp;Bilbrey a key contributor to the Board on a wide range of issues.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
