<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:7.5pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>Former Vice Chairman, Pfizer Inc., a pharmaceutical, consumer and animal products health company (July 2005 to December 2007)</B></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:7.5pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><B><I>QUALIFICATIONS, ATTRIBUTES AND SKILLS</I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:7.5pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Mr.&nbsp;Shedlarz spent the majority of his professional career with Pfizer. At the time
of his retirement in 2007, Mr.&nbsp;Shedlarz was responsible for operations including the animal health business, finance, accounting, strategic planning, business development, global sourcing, manufacturing, information systems and human resources,
skills that are particularly valuable to the Board given his role as chair of the Finance and Risk Management Committee. Mr.&nbsp;Shedlarz also brings to our Board considerable international business and leadership experience he gained while at
Pfizer.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:7.5pt">
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:7.5pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><B><I>PREVIOUS BUSINESS EXPERIENCE</I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:7.5pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;<FONT STYLE="font-size:5pt">&nbsp;</FONT>Executive Vice President and Chief Financial Officer,
Pfizer Inc. (January 1999 to July 2005)</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:7.5pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><B><I>CURRENT PUBLIC
AND OTHER KEY DIRECTORSHIPS</I></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:7.5pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;<FONT STYLE="font-size:5pt">&nbsp;</FONT>Teladoc, Inc. (September 2016 to present)</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:7.5pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;<FONT STYLE="font-size:5pt">&nbsp;</FONT>Pitney Bowes, Inc. (May 2001 to present)</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:7.5pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;<FONT STYLE="font-size:5pt">&nbsp;</FONT>Teachers Insurance and Annuity Association Board of
Trustees (March 2007 to present)</P> <P STYLE="font-size:8pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:7.5pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><B><I>EDUCATION</I></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:7.5pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;<FONT STYLE="font-size:5pt">&nbsp;</FONT>Bachelor&#146;s degree in economics and mathematics from
Oakland/Michigan State University</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:7.5pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;<FONT STYLE="font-size:5pt">&nbsp;</FONT>Masters of Business
Administration degree in finance and accounting from the New York University, Leonard N. Stern School of Business</P></TD></TR>
</TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">27 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><B><A NAME="toc348571_14"></A><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">NON-EMPLOYEE</FONT> DIRECTOR
COMPENSATION </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>The Hershey Company Directors&#146; Compensation Plan </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">We maintain a Directors&#146; Compensation Plan that is designed to: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Attract and retain highly qualified, <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> directors; and </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Align the interests of <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> directors with those of our stockholders by paying a portion of <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> compensation in units
representing shares of our Common Stock. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Directors who are employees of the Company receive no additional compensation for their service on
our Board. Mr.&nbsp;Bilbrey, our current Chairman of the Board, is the only employee of the Company who also served as a director during 2016 and thus received no additional compensation for his Board service. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Board targets <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> director compensation at the 50<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">th</SUP>
percentile of compensation paid to directors at a peer group of companies we call the 2016 Peer Group. Information about the 2016 Peer Group is included in the section entitled &#147;Setting Compensation&#148; in the Compensation
Discussion&nbsp;&amp; Analysis. Each year, with the assistance of the Compensation Committee and the Compensation Committee&#146;s compensation consultant, the Board reviews the compensation paid to directors at companies in the current peer group
to determine whether any changes to <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> director compensation are warranted. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">As a result of its review in
December 2015, the Board determined that no changes to <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> director compensation were warranted for 2016. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Accordingly, compensation paid to <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> directors in 2016 was as follows: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="76%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">

<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:7.5pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(1)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Paid in addition to $100,000 annual retainer for <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> directors. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Board completed its annual review of <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> director compensation in December 2016 and determined that the
following changes were warranted for 2017 to ensure that the program remains aligned to the 50<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">th</SUP> percentile of compensation paid to directors from our 2016 Peer Group. The Board elected to
increase the annual RSU award from $135,000 to $150,000 and to increase the annual Governance Committee Chair retainer from $10,000 to $15,000. The Board also elected to increase the <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> director
stock ownership guidelines, as described below, from four times the annual retainer to five times the annual retainer. Except for these changes, all other elements of the <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> director compensation
program described above remain unchanged for 2017. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">28 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>Payment of Annual Retainer, Lead Independent Director Fee and Committee Chair Fees </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The annual retainer and any applicable Lead Independent Director or committee chair fees for all <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> directors
are paid in quarterly installments on the 15<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">th </SUP>day of March, June, September and December, or the prior business day if the 15<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">th</SUP> is not a
business day. <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Non-employee</FONT> directors may elect to receive all or a portion of the annual retainer in cash or in Common Stock. <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Non-employee</FONT> directors may also elect to
defer receipt of all or a portion of the retainer, Lead Independent Director fee or committee chair fees until the date their membership on the Board ends. Lead Independent Director and committee chair fees that are not deferred are paid only in
cash. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Non-employee</FONT> directors choosing to defer all or a portion of their retainer, Lead Independent Director fee
or committee chair fees may invest the deferred amounts in two ways: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">In a cash account that values the performance of the investment based upon the performance of one or more third-party investment funds selected by the director from among the mutual funds or other investment options
available to all employees participating in our 401(k) Plan. Amounts invested in the cash account are paid only in cash. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">In a deferred common stock unit account that we value according to the performance of our Common Stock, including reinvested dividends. Amounts invested in the deferred common stock unit account are paid in shares of
Common Stock. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>Restricted Stock Units </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">RSUs are granted quarterly to <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> directors on the first day of January, April, July and October. In 2016, the
number of RSUs granted in each quarter was determined by dividing $33,750 by the average closing price of a share of our Common Stock on the New York Stock Exchange (&#147;NYSE&#148;) on the last three trading days preceding the grant date. RSUs
awarded to <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> directors vest one year after the date of grant, or earlier upon termination of the director&#146;s membership on the Board by reason of retirement (termination of service from the
Board after the director&#146;s 60<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">th</SUP> birthday), death or disability, for any reason after a Change in Control as defined in our Executive Benefits Protection Plan (Group 3A) (&#147;EBPP 3A&#148;),
or under such other circumstances as the Board may determine. Vested RSUs are payable to directors in shares of Common Stock or, at the option of the director, can be deferred as common stock units under the Directors&#146; Compensation Plan until
the director&#146;s membership on the Board ends. Dividend equivalent units are credited at regular rates on the RSUs during the restriction period and, upon vesting of the RSUs, are payable in shares of Common Stock or deferred as common stock
units together with any RSUs the director has deferred. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">As of March&nbsp;6, 2017, Messrs. Davis, Malcolm, Mead, Nevels, Ridge and Shedlarz and
Mmes.&nbsp;Arway and Haben had attained retirement age for purposes of the vesting of RSUs. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>Other Compensation, Reimbursements and Programs </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Board occasionally establishes committees of limited duration for special purposes. When a special committee is established, the Board will determine
whether to provide <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> directors with additional compensation for service on such committee based on the expected duties of the committee, the anticipated number and length of any committee meetings,
and other factors the Board, in its discretion, may deem relevant. In 2016, the Board approved payments of $25,000 to Ms.&nbsp;Arway as Chair and $20,000 to each of Ms.&nbsp;Haben and Messrs. Malcolm, Mead, Nevels and Shedlarz for their service on
the special committee established in connection with the Company&#146;s Chief Executive Officer search. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">29 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">We reimburse our directors for travel and other
<FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">out-of-pocket</FONT></FONT> expenses they incur when attending Board and committee meetings and for minor incidental expenses they incur when performing directors&#146; services. We
also provide reimbursement for at least one director continuing education program each year. Directors receive travel accident insurance while traveling on the Company&#146;s business and receive discounts on the purchase of our products to the same
extent and on the same terms as our employees. Directors also are eligible to participate in the Company&#146;s Gift Matching Program. Under the Gift Matching Program, the Company will match, upon a director&#146;s request, contributions made by the
director to one or more charitable organizations, on a <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">dollar-for-dollar</FONT></FONT> basis up to a maximum aggregate contribution of $5,000 annually. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>Stock Ownership Guidelines </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Pursuant to the Board&#146;s
Corporate Governance Guidelines, <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> directors are expected to own shares of Common Stock having a value equal to at least five times the annual retainer. Each
<FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> director has until January&nbsp;1 of the year following his or her fifth anniversary of becoming a director to satisfy the guideline. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Compensation Committee reviews the stock ownership guidelines annually to ensure they are aligned with external market comparisons. Prior to December 2016,
<FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> directors were expected to own shares of Common Stock having a value equal to at least four times the annual retainer. As part of the annual review completed in December 2016, the Board, upon the
recommendation of the Compensation Committee, elected to increase the <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> director stock ownership guidelines from four times the annual retainer to five times the annual retainer. Under the
Board&#146;s Corporate Governance Guidelines, each <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> director serving on the Board as of the date of the increase has until January&nbsp;1, 2019 to satisfy the new stock ownership guidelines. Any <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> director serving on the Board that had not yet reached his or her initial compliance date as of the date of the increase has until the second anniversary of such initial compliance date to satisfy the
new stock ownership guidelines. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>2016 Director Compensation </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The following table and explanatory footnotes provide information with respect to the compensation paid or provided to
<FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> directors during 2016: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">


<TR>
<TD WIDTH="42%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="4%"></TD>

under the Directors&#146; Compensation Plan are based on investment options available to all participants in our 401(k) Plan or our Common Stock and, accordingly, the earnings credited during 2016 were not considered &#147;above market&#148; or
&#147;preferential&#148; earnings. </TD></TR></TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">30 </P>

<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">*</TD>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Less than 1% </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:7.5pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:7.5pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">*</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Director </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>Information Regarding Our Controlling Stockholder </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">In 1909, Milton S. and Catherine S. Hershey established a trust having as its sole beneficiary Milton Hershey School, a
<FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-profit</FONT> school for the full-time care and education of disadvantaged children located in Hershey, Pennsylvania. Hershey Trust Company, a state-chartered trust company, is trustee of the Milton Hershey
School Trust. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">34 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">In its capacity as trustee for the Milton Hershey School Trust, Hershey Trust Company is our controlling
stockholder. In this capacity, it will have the right to cast 8.4% of all of the votes entitled to be cast on matters requiring the vote of the Common Stock voting separately and 81.6% of all of the votes entitled to be cast on matters requiring the
vote of the Common Stock and Class&nbsp;B Common Stock voting together. The board of directors of Hershey Trust Company, with the approval of the board of managers (governing body) of Milton Hershey School, decides how funds held by Hershey Trust
Company, as trustee for the Milton Hershey School Trust, will be invested. The board of directors of Hershey Trust Company generally decides how shares of The Hershey Company held by Hershey Trust Company, as trustee for the Milton Hershey School
Trust, will be voted. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">As of the Record Date, Hershey Trust Company also held 149,500 shares of our Common Stock as investments. The board of directors or
management of Hershey Trust Company decides how these shares will be voted. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">In all, Hershey Trust Company, as trustee for the Milton Hershey School Trust
and as direct owner of investment shares, will be entitled to vote 12,903,021 shares of our Common Stock and 60,612,012 shares of our Class&nbsp;B Common Stock at the Annual Meeting. Stated in terms of voting power, Hershey Trust Company will have
the right to cast 8.5% of all of the votes entitled to be cast on matters requiring the vote of the Common Stock voting separately and 81.6% of all of the votes entitled to be cast on matters requiring the vote of the Common Stock and Class&nbsp;B
Common Stock voting together at the Annual Meeting. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Our certificate of incorporation contains the following important provisions regarding our
Class&nbsp;B Common Stock: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">All holders of Class&nbsp;B Common Stock, including Hershey Trust Company, as trustee for Milton Hershey School, may convert any of their Class&nbsp;B Common Stock shares into shares of our Common Stock at any time on a
<FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">share-for-share</FONT></FONT> basis. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">All shares of Class&nbsp;B Common Stock will automatically be converted to shares of Common Stock on a <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">share-for-share</FONT></FONT> basis if Hershey
Trust Company, as trustee for Milton Hershey School, or any successor trustee, or Milton Hershey School, as appropriate, ceases to hold more than 50% of the total Class&nbsp;B Common Stock shares outstanding and at least 15% of the total Common
Stock and Class&nbsp;B Common Stock shares outstanding. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">We must obtain the approval of Hershey Trust Company, as trustee for Milton Hershey School, or any successor trustee, or Milton Hershey School, as appropriate, before we issue any Common Stock or take any other action
that would deprive Hershey Trust Company, as trustee for Milton Hershey School, or any successor trustee, or Milton Hershey School, as appropriate, of the ability to cast a majority of the votes on any matter where the Class&nbsp;B Common Stock is
entitled to vote, either separately as a class or together with any other class. </TD></TR></TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">35 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><B><A NAME="toc348571_16"></A>AUDIT COMMITTEE REPORT </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>To Our Stockholders: </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Audit Committee is currently
comprised of four directors, each of whom is considered independent under the NYSE Rules and the rules and regulations of the SEC. The Board has determined that each member of the Audit Committee is financially literate and that each of Messrs.
Davis, Mead and Nevels qualifies as an &#147;audit committee financial expert,&#148; as that term is defined under the rules promulgated by the SEC. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Our
role as the Audit Committee is to assist the Board in its oversight of: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">The integrity of the Company&#146;s financial statements; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">The Company&#146;s compliance with legal and regulatory requirements; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">The independent auditors&#146; qualifications and independence; and </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">The performance of the independent auditors and the Company&#146;s internal audit function. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Audit
Committee operates under a written charter that was last reviewed by the Audit Committee on December&nbsp;5, 2016. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Our duties as an Audit Committee
include overseeing the Company&#146;s management, internal auditors and independent auditors in their performance of the following functions, for which they are responsible: </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Management </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Preparing the Company&#146;s financial statements; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Establishing effective financial reporting systems and internal controls and procedures; and </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Reporting on the effectiveness of the Company&#146;s internal control over financial reporting. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Internal Audit Department </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Independently assessing management&#146;s system of internal controls and procedures; and </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Reporting on the effectiveness of that system. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Independent Auditors </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Auditing the Company&#146;s financial statements; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Expressing an opinion about the financial statements&#146; conformity with U.S. generally accepted accounting principles; and </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Annually auditing the effectiveness of the Company&#146;s internal control over financial reporting. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">We meet
periodically with management, the internal auditors and independent auditors, independently and collectively, to discuss the quality of the Company&#146;s financial reporting process and the adequacy and effectiveness of the Company&#146;s internal
controls. Prior to the Company filing its Annual Report on Form <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">10-K</FONT> for the year ended December&nbsp;31, 2016 with the SEC, we also: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Reviewed and discussed the audited financial statements with management and the independent auditors; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Discussed with the independent auditors the matters required to be discussed by applicable requirements of the Public Company Accounting Oversight Board; </TD></TR></TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">36 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">


<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Received the written disclosures and the letter from the independent auditors in accordance with applicable requirements of the Public Company Accounting Oversight Board regarding the independent auditors&#146;
communications with the Audit Committee concerning independence; and </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Discussed with the independent auditors their independence from the Company. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">We are not employees of the
Company and are not performing the functions of auditors or accountants. We are not responsible as an Audit Committee or individually to conduct &#147;field work&#148; or other types of auditing or accounting reviews or procedures or to set auditor
independence standards. In carrying out our duties as Audit Committee members, we have relied on the information provided to us by management and the independent auditors. Consequently, we do not assure that the audit of the Company&#146;s financial
statements has been carried out in accordance with generally accepted auditing standards, that the financial statements are presented in accordance with U.S. generally accepted accounting principles or that the Company&#146;s auditors are in fact
&#147;independent.&#148; </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Based on the reports and discussions described in this report, and subject to the limitations on our role and responsibilities
as an Audit Committee referred to above and in our charter, we recommended to the Board that the audited financial statements be included in the Company&#146;s Annual Report on <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Form&nbsp;10-K</FONT> for the year
ended December&nbsp;31, 2016, filed with the SEC on February&nbsp;21, 2017. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:54%; text-indent:-2%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>Submitted by the Audit Committee:</B>
</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:54%; text-indent:-2%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Charles&nbsp;A. Davis, Chair </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:54%; text-indent:-2%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Pamela M. Arway </P>

<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:7.5pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="8%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(1)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Fees associated primarily with services related to due diligence for potential business acquisitions, auditing of <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">carve-out</FONT> financial statements and auditing of employee benefit
plans. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:7.5pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="8%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(2)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Fees pertaining primarily to tax consultation and tax compliance services. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Audit Committee <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">pre-approves</FONT> all audit, audit-related and <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-audit</FONT> services performed by the independent auditors. The Audit Committee is authorized by its charter to delegate to one or more
of its members the authority to <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">pre-approve</FONT> any audit, audit-related or <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-audit</FONT> services, provided that the approval is presented to the Audit Committee at its next
scheduled meeting. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Audit Committee <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">pre-approved</FONT> all services provided by KPMG in 2016. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">On April&nbsp;21, 2016, upon the approval of the Audit Committee, we notified KPMG that it would be dismissed as our independent auditors effective upon the
completion of KPMG&#146;s audit of the Company&#146;s consolidated financial statements for the fiscal year ending December&nbsp;31, 2016 (and the effectiveness of internal control over financial reporting as of December&nbsp;31, 2016), and the
issuance of their report thereon. The decision to dismiss KPMG was made as part of a competitive bidding process to determine the Company&#146;s independent registered public accounting firm for the fiscal year ending December&nbsp;31, 2017. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The audit reports of KPMG on the Company&#146;s consolidated financial statements as of and for the years ended December&nbsp;31, 2016 and 2015 did not contain
any adverse opinion or disclaimer of opinion, nor were they qualified or modified as to uncertainty, audit scope or accounting principles. The audit reports of KPMG on the effectiveness of internal control over financial reporting as of
December&nbsp;31, 2016 and 2015 did not contain any adverse opinion or disclaimer of opinion, nor were they qualified or modified as to uncertainty, audit scope, or accounting principles, except that KPMG&#146;s report indicates that the Company did
not maintain effective internal control over financial reporting as of December&nbsp;31, 2015, because of the effect of a material weakness related to the Company&#146;s accounting for cocoa derivative instruments. During the Company&#146;s two most
recent fiscal years ended December&nbsp;31, 2016 and December&nbsp;31, 2015, there were no (1)&nbsp;disagreements with KPMG on any matter of accounting principles or practices, financial statement disclosures, or auditing scope or procedures, which
disagreements, if not resolved to the satisfaction of KPMG, would have caused KPMG to make reference to the subject matter of the disagreements in connection with its reports; and (2)&nbsp;events of the type listed in paragraphs (A)&nbsp;through (D)
of Item 304(a)(1)(v) of Regulation <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">S-K,</FONT> except for the material weakness as described in this paragraph. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">38 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">On June&nbsp;15, 2016, the Audit Committee appointed Ernst&nbsp;&amp; Young LLP as the Company&#146;s independent
registered public accounting firm for the Company&#146;s fiscal year ending December&nbsp;31, 2017. During the Company&#146;s two most recent fiscal years ended December&nbsp;31, 2016 and 2015, neither the Company nor anyone acting on its behalf
consulted with Ernst&nbsp;&amp; Young LLP regarding either: (i)&nbsp;the application of accounting principles to a specified transaction, either completed or proposed; or the type of audit opinion that might be rendered on the Company&#146;s
financial statements, and neither a written report nor oral advice was provided to the Company that Ernst&nbsp;&amp; Young LLP concluded was an important factor considered by the Company in reaching a decision as to the accounting, auditing or
financial reporting issue; or (ii)&nbsp;any matter that was either the subject of a disagreement (as defined in paragraph (a)(1)(iv) of Item 304 of Regulation <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">S-K</FONT> and the related instructions thereto) or a
reportable event (as described in paragraph (a)(1)(v) of Item 304 of Regulation <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">S-K).</FONT> </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">39 </P>

APPOINTMENT </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><B>OF INDEPENDENT AUDITORS </B></FONT></P>

</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Audit Committee has appointed Ernst&nbsp;&amp; Young LLP as the Company&#146;s independent auditors for 2017. Although not
required to do so, the Board, upon the Audit Committee&#146;s recommendation, has determined to submit the Audit Committee&#146;s appointment of Ernst&nbsp;&amp; Young LLP as our independent auditors to stockholders for ratification as a matter of
good corporate governance. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Audit Committee&#146;s appointment of Ernst&nbsp;&amp; Young LLP as the Company&#146;s independent auditors for 2017 will
be considered ratified if a majority of the shares of the Common Stock and Class&nbsp;B Common Stock (voting together without regard to class) present and entitled to vote at the Annual Meeting are voted for the proposal. If stockholders do not
ratify the appointment of Ernst&nbsp;&amp; Young LLP as the Company&#146;s independent auditors for 2017, the Audit Committee will reconsider its appointment. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Representatives of both Ernst&nbsp;&amp; Young LLP and KPMG (our independent auditors for the fiscal year ended December&nbsp;31, 2016) will attend the Annual
Meeting, will have the opportunity to make a statement, if they so desire, and will respond to questions. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">40 </P>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><B><A NAME="toc348571_19"></A>COMPENSATION DISCUSSION&nbsp;&amp; ANALYSIS
</B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><B><A NAME="toc348571_20"></A>EXECUTIVE COMPENSATION </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">This section discusses and analyzes the decisions we made concerning the compensation of our named executive officers (&#147;NEOs&#148;) for 2016. It also
describes the process for determining executive compensation and the factors considered in determining the amount of compensation awarded to our NEOs. Our NEOs for 2016 are: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>Executive Summary </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><I>2016 Highlights </I></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:8pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Hershey Company (the &#147;Company&#148;), headquartered in Hershey, Pa., is a global confectionery leader known for bringing goodness to the world through
its chocolate, sweets, mints and other great-tasting snacks. We have approximately 17,980 employees around the world who work every day to deliver delicious, quality products. We have more than 80 brands that drive approximately $7.4&nbsp;billion in
annual revenues. Building on its core business, the Company is expanding its portfolio to include a broader range of delicious snacks. The Company remains focused on growing its presence in key international markets while continuing to extend its
competitive advantage in North America. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">In January 2016, we announced the following Company expectations, which are substantially reflected in our 2016
incentive programs: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Increase constant currency net sales<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(1)</SUP> around 3% from 2015; and </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Increase adjusted earnings per share-diluted<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(2)</SUP> about 6% from 2015. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="line-height:8.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1.00pt solid #000000;width:21%">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:7.5pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(1)</SUP>&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">While we report our financial results in accordance with U.S. generally accepted accounting principles (&#147;GAAP&#148;), we also use <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-GAAP</FONT> financial measures within
Management&#146;s Discussion and Analysis in the 2016 Annual Report on Form <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">10-K</FONT> that accompanies this Proxy Statement in order to provide additional information to investors to facilitate the comparison of
past and present performance. Some of the financial targets under our short- and long-term incentive programs are also based on <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-GAAP</FONT> financial measures. <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Non-GAAP</FONT>
financial measures are used by management in evaluating results of operations internally and in assessing the impact of known trends and uncertainties on our business, but they are not intended to replace the presentation of financial results in
accordance with GAAP. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:7.5pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Constant currency net sales is a <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-GAAP</FONT> financial measure. To calculate net sales on a constant currency basis, net sales for the current fiscal year period for entities
reporting in currencies other than the U.S. dollar are translated into U.S. dollars at the average rates during the comparable period of the prior fiscal year. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:7.5pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(2)</SUP>&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Adjusted earnings per share-diluted is a <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-GAAP</FONT> financial measure. We define adjusted earnings per share-diluted as diluted earnings per share of the Company&#146;s common stock
(&#147;Common Stock&#148;), excluding unallocated <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">mark-to-market</FONT></FONT> losses on commodity derivatives, costs associated with business realignment activities, costs relating
to the integration of acquisitions, <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-service</FONT> related components of our pension expense (income) (&#147;NSRPE(I)&#148;), goodwill and other intangible asset impairment charges, settlement of the Shanghai
Golden Monkey liability in conjunction with the purchase of the remaining 20% of the outstanding shares of Shanghai Golden Monkey, the gain realized on the sale of a trademark, costs associated with the early extinguishment of debt and other <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-recurring</FONT> gains and losses. </TD></TR></TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">41 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">In April 2016, we lowered our guidance for our expected 2016 constant currency net sales increase to 2.5% and for
our expected 2016 adjusted earnings per share-diluted increase to 3% to 4%. See the section entitled &#147;Annual Incentives&#148; for more information regarding our 2016 annual incentive targets and related results. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Actual results for 2016 were as follows: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt" ALIGN="center">


<IMG SRC="g348571g96x06.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
 </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">While we did not meet our expectations for net sales growth, we exceeded our adjusted earnings per share-diluted
expectations. Because of our mixed financial performance results, our NEOs earned significantly below-target performance stock unit (&#147;PSU&#148;) payouts and slightly above-target annual cash incentive awards, as described further in the
sections entitled &#147;Long-Term Incentives&#148; and &#147;Annual Incentives.&#148; </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:8pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><I>Hershey Has Strong <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Pay-for-Performance</FONT></FONT> Alignment </I></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:8pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Compensation and Executive Organization Committee (the &#147;Compensation
Committee&#148;) of our Board of Directors (the &#147;Board&#148;) has oversight responsibility for our executive compensation framework and for aligning our executives&#146; pay with the Company&#146;s performance. We believe we have a strong <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">pay-for-performance</FONT></FONT> alignment because a significant portion of each NEO&#146;s target total direct compensation is tied to the financial performance of the Company as well as
shareholder returns. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">In 2016, approximately 70% of our CEO&#146;s and 60% of our other NEOs&#146; target total direct compensation was variable and tied
to Company performance, including a substantial portion tied to shareholder value. Specifically, 34% of our PSUs were tied to Total Shareholder Return (&#147;TSR&#148;). Combined with the other financial and strategic metrics that determine our
NEOs&#146; compensation, we have aligned our executive compensation program with the long-term interests of our stockholders. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">42 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Over the last three years, we have delivered a TSR of 14%, which is at the bottom of our Financial Peer Group
described in the section entitled &#147;Performance Stock Unit Targets and Results.&#148; </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt" ALIGN="center">


<IMG SRC="g348571g49_06.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
 </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:8pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Because our TSR metric was below threshold for the 2014-2016 PSU cycle, our NEOs received a 0% payout for this metric,
significantly reducing their overall PSU payout, as described in more detail in the section entitled &#147;Performance Stock Unit Targets and Results.&#148; </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:8pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><I>Our Stockholders Strongly Approve of Our Pay Practices </I></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:8pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Last year, our stockholders overwhelmingly approved our <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">&#147;say-on-pay&#148;</FONT></FONT>
resolution, with more than 93% of the votes cast by the holders of Common Stock and more than 99% of the combined votes cast by the holders of the Common Stock and Class&nbsp;B Common Stock voting in favor. Our Compensation Committee believes the
results of last year&#146;s <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">&#147;say-on-pay&#148;</FONT></FONT> vote affirmed our stockholders&#146; support of our Company&#146;s executive compensation program. Consequentially,
our approach to executive compensation in 2016 was substantially the same as the approach stockholders approved in 2015. In keeping with the preference expressed by our stockholders at the 2011 Annual Meeting of Stockholders, our Board has committed
to having an annual <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">&#147;say-on-pay&#148;</FONT></FONT> vote as described in Proposal No.&nbsp;3 &#150; Approval of Named Executive Officer Compensation on a <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Non-Binding</FONT> Advisory Basis. We are asking stockholders to express a preference for the frequency of the <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">&#147;say-on-pay&#148;</FONT></FONT> vote,
pursuant to Section 14A of the Exchange Act, in this proxy statement. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">We believe our compensation and governance policies and practices are significant
drivers of our stockholder support. These policies and practices include: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B>Pay for performance.</B> A substantial percentage of each of our NEO&#146;s target total direct compensation is variable, performance-based compensation. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B>Performance measures support strategic objectives.</B> The performance measures we use for our variable, performance-based compensation reflect strategic and operating objectives, creating long-term value for our
stockholders. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B>Appropriate risk-taking.</B> We set performance goals that consider our publicly-announced financial expectations, which we believe will encourage appropriate risk taking. Our incentive programs are appropriately
capped so as not to encourage excessive risk taking. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B>No tax <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">gross-ups.</FONT></B> We do not provide tax <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">gross-ups,</FONT> except for relocation expenses. </TD></TR></TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">43 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">


<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B>&#147;Double-trigger&#148; benefits in the event of a change in control.</B> In the event of a change in control, the payment of severance benefits and the acceleration of vesting of time-based long-term incentive
awards are &#147;double-trigger&#148; benefits. The severance payments and accelerated vesting of continuing incentive awards will not occur unless there is also a qualifying termination of employment upon or within two years following the change in
control. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B>No <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">re-pricings</FONT> or exchanges of underwater stock options.</B> Our stockholder-approved Equity and Incentive Compensation Plan (&#147;EICP&#148;) prohibits <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">re-pricing</FONT> or exchange of underwater stock options without stockholder approval. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B>Do not provide excessive perquisites. </B>Executive perquisites are kept to a minimal level relative to a NEO&#146;s total compensation and do not play a significant role in our executive compensation program.
</TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B>Do not provide for the prepayment of dividends on unearned PSUs. </B>Dividends are not paid on PSU awards during the three-year performance cycle. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B>Significant stock ownership guidelines.</B> Our NEOs and other executives are required to accumulate and hold stock equal to a multiple of base salary. If an executive has not met his or her ownership requirement in
a timely manner, the executive is required to retain a portion of shares received under long-term incentive awards until the requirements are met. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B>Anti-hedging policy.</B> Our NEOs, directors and other insiders are prohibited from entering into hedging transactions related to our stock. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B>Anti-pledging policy.</B> Our NEOs, directors and other insiders are prohibited from entering into pledging transactions related to our stock. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><B>&#149;</B></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B>Clawbacks and other covenants. </B></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="9%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL"><SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#161;</FONT></SUP>&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">For the protection of the Company, we require our NEOs to enter into an Employee Confidentiality and Restrictive Covenant Agreement (&#147;ECRCA&#148;) as a condition of receipt of long-term incentive awards. Failure to
comply with the ECRCA may subject the employee to cancellation of awards and a requirement to repay amounts received from awards. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
