received by the NEOs with respect to PSU and RSU awards that vested in 2016 is included in Columns&nbsp;(d)&nbsp;and&nbsp;(e) of the 2016 Option Exercises and Stock Vested Table. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:7.5pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(5)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Column (f)&nbsp;presents the grant date fair value of stock options awarded to the NEOs for the years indicated and does not reflect the value of shares actually received or which may be received in the future with
respect to such stock options. The assumptions we made to determine the value of these awards are set forth in Note 10 to the Company&#146;s Consolidated Financial Statements included in our 2016 Annual Report on Form
<FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">10-K</FONT> that accompanies this Proxy Statement. The number of stock options awarded to each NEO during 2016 appears in Column (j)&nbsp;of the 2016 Grants of Plan-Based Awards Table. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:7.5pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(6)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Column (g)&nbsp;reflects the OHIP payments made to each NEO based upon actual salary received in 2016. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:7.5pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(7)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Column (h)&nbsp;reflects the aggregate change in the actuarial present value of the NEO&#146;s retirement benefit under the Company&#146;s pension plan and the DB SERP. The change in value calculation uses the same
discount rate and mortality rate assumptions as the 2015 and 2016 audited financial statements, as applicable, and measures the change in value between the pension plan measurement date in the 2015 and 2016 audited financial statements. The change
in value during a year is primarily driven by three factors: 1) changes in valuation assumptions; 2) changes in the NEO&#146;s pensionable earnings; and 3) an additional year of service and age. During 2014, each of these factors contributed
significantly to the increase in the pension value. During 2015, the primary driver of the increase in pension value was the additional year of age and service. The impact of changes in valuation assumptions and pensionable earnings during 2015 were
relatively smaller and mostly offsetting. During 2016, each of the three factors driving change caused a minor increase to the pension value. The impact when combining each of the three minor increases resulted in a relatively larger increase to the
pension value. The amounts in Column (h)&nbsp;do not reflect amounts paid or that might be paid to the NEO. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:7.5pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Mmes. Little and Turner and Mr.&nbsp;O&#146;Day participate in the DC&nbsp;SERP rather than the DB&nbsp;SERP. The DC&nbsp;SERP is established under the Company&#146;s Deferred Compensation Plan. DC&nbsp;SERP
contributions for Mmes. Little and Turner and Mr.&nbsp;O&#146;Day are included in Column&nbsp;(i) as explained in more detail in footnote&nbsp;(8) below. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:7.5pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">The NEOs also participate in our <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-qualified,</FONT> <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-funded</FONT> Deferred Compensation Plan under which deferred amounts are credited with
notional earnings based on the performance of one or more third-party investment options available to all participants in our 401(k) plan. No portion of the notional earnings credited during 2016 was &#147;above market&#148; or
&#147;preferential.&#148; Consequently, no Deferred Compensation Plan earnings are included in amounts reported in Column&nbsp;(h)&nbsp;above. See the 2016 Pension Benefits Table and the 2016 <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Non-Qualified</FONT>
Deferred Compensation Table for more information on the benefits payable to the NEOs under the pension plan, DB&nbsp;SERP and Deferred Compensation Plan. </TD></TR></TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">63 </P>

<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(8)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">All other compensation includes amounts as described below: </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV ALIGN="right">

<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:7.5pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(a)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Employees who earn over the IRS compensation limit and/or defer any portion of their OHIP award are eligible for the Supplemental 401(k) Match, contingent on the employee contributing an amount to the 401(k) plan equal
to the annual <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">pre-tax</FONT> limit established by the IRS. Messrs. Bilbrey and O&#146;Day and Mmes. Little, Buck, and Turner are eligible to receive a Supplemental 401(k) Match Contribution equal to 4.5% of the
amount by which their eligible earnings (salary and OHIP) exceeds the IRS compensation limit. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:7.5pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(b)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">As are all new hires of the Company since January&nbsp;1, 2007, Mmes. Little and Turner and Mr.&nbsp;O&#146;Day are eligible to receive a contribution to their 401(k) plan account equal to 3% of base salary and OHIP up
to the maximum amount permitted by the IRS. We call this contribution the Core Retirement Contribution (&#147;CRC&#148;). They also are eligible to receive a Supplemental Core Retirement Contribution (&#147;Supplemental CRC&#148;) equal to 3% of the
amount by which their eligible earnings (salary and OHIP) exceeds the IRS compensation limit. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:7.5pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(c)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">The value of any personal use of Company aircraft by the NEOs is based on the Company&#146;s aggregate incremental <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">per-flight</FONT> hour cost for the aircraft used and flight time of
the applicable flight. The incremental <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">per-flight</FONT> hour cost is calculated by reference to fuel, maintenance (labor and parts), crew, landing and parking expenses. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:7.5pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(d)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">From time to time the Company provides security services for Mr.&nbsp;Bilbrey when the Company determines that conditions warrant such services for the safety and protection of Mr.&nbsp;Bilbrey and his family. The
amount reported is the Company&#146;s incremental cost for such services. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:7.5pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(e)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">For Mr.&nbsp;O&#146;Day, reflects payment for relocation expenses and related taxes incurred in years prior to 2016, but not billed until 2016. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:7.5pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(f)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Reflects attorney fees paid or incurred in connection with the negotiation of Mr.&nbsp;Bilbrey&#146;s retirement agreement. </TD></TR></TABLE>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">The threshold amount is the amount that would have been payable had the minimum individual performance score been achieved and the Company performance score been zero. The target amount is the amount that would have
been payable had the business and individual performance scores been 100% on all metrics. The maximum amount is the amount that would have been payable had the maximum score been achieved on all metrics. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

the 2015-2017 performance cycle and, with the exception of Ms.&nbsp;Little, the 2016 adjusted earnings per share-diluted component of the 2014-2016 performance cycle. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

2014-2016 performance cycles will depend upon achievement against the metrics explained in the Compensation Discussion&nbsp;&amp; Analysis in the section entitled &#147;Performance Stock Unit Targets and Results.&#148; </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Payment, if any, will be made in shares of the Company&#146;s Common Stock at the conclusion of the three-year performance cycle. The Compensation Committee will approve the targets for the annual adjusted
earnings&nbsp;per&nbsp;share-diluted metrics at the beginning of each of the three years in the performance cycle. The minimum award as shown in Column&nbsp;(f)&nbsp;is the number of shares payable for achievement of the threshold level of
performance on one of the metrics and the maximum award as shown in Column&nbsp;(h) is the number of shares payable for achievement of the maximum level of performance on all metrics. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

STYLE="white-space:nowrap">one-quarter</FONT> of the executive&#146;s long-term incentive target percentage times his or her 2016 base salary, divided by the closing price of the Company&#146;s Common Stock on the NYSE on the award date ($90.39) for
each NEO. The actual number of RSUs awarded varied from the target level based on the executive&#146;s performance evaluation for the year ended December&nbsp;31, 2015. Annual RSU awards vest in thirds over three years. </TD></TR></TABLE>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">For Messrs. Bilbrey and O&#146;Day and Ms.&nbsp;Buck, the number in Column (d), and for Ms.&nbsp;Turner, the first number in Column (d), includes the number of PSUs earned from the 2014-2016 performance cycle that ended
on December&nbsp;31, 2016, as determined by the Compensation Committee, or, in the case of Mr.&nbsp;Bilbrey, by the independent members of our Board. The aggregate results of the 2014-2016 performance cycle exceeded the financial thresholds, but did
not meet the financial targets, established at the start of the performance cycle; therefore, the number of PSUs included in Column (d)&nbsp;reflects payment at 20.66% of target. All of the applicable NEOs received payment of the award in Common
Stock in February 2017. In accordance with the terms of the PSU award agreement, each PSU represents one share of our Common Stock valued in Column (e)&nbsp;at $107.95 the closing price of our Common Stock on the NYSE on February&nbsp;22, 2017, the
date the Compensation Committee approved the PSU payment. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:7.5pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(3)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">For Ms.&nbsp;Little, the number in Column (d)&nbsp;reflects RSUs that were distributed in 2016 from a 2015 award and the number in Column (e)&nbsp;sets forth the value of such RSUs at vesting on May&nbsp;15, 2016 and
cash credits equivalent to dividends accrued during the vesting period. Ms.&nbsp;Little elected to defer 100% of this award. As a result, on the vesting date of these RSUs, because the cash credits earned for the 4,135 shares deferred did not exceed
the tax liability associated with those shares, 43 shares were liquidated to cover the tax liability. The remaining 4,092 shares were credited to Ms.&nbsp;Little&#146;s Deferred Compensation account and she received a cash payment for the remaining
liquidated share value (less cash withheld to meet tax obligations). </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:7.5pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(4)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">For Ms.&nbsp;Turner, the second number in Column (d)&nbsp;reflects RSUs that were distributed in 2016 from a 2012 award and the second number in Column (e)&nbsp;sets forth the value of such RSUs at vesting on
July&nbsp;9, 2016 and cash credits equivalent to dividends accrued during the vesting period. Ms.&nbsp;Turner elected to defer 80% of this award and to receive immediate payment in shares of the Company&#146;s Common Stock for 20% of this award. As
a result, on the vesting date of these RSUs, Ms.&nbsp;Turner received immediate payment of 1,400 RSUs and their respective dividends (less cash and shares withheld to meet tax obligations). Because the cash credits earned for the 5,600 shares
deferred exceeded the tax liability associated with those shares, the 5,600 shares were credited to Ms.&nbsp;Turner&#146;s Deferred Compensation account and she received a cash payment for the remaining dividend value (less cash withheld to meet tax
obligations). </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B><A NAME="toc348571_38"></A>2016 Pension Benefits Table </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Mr.&nbsp;Bilbrey and Ms.&nbsp;Buck are participants in our pension plan and are fully vested in benefits under that plan. Mr.&nbsp;Bilbrey and Ms.&nbsp;Buck
are also eligible to participate in our <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-qualified</FONT> DB&nbsp;SERP. No benefit is payable under the DB&nbsp;SERP if the executive officer terminates employment prior to age 55 or if he or she does not have
five years of service with the Company. As of December&nbsp;31,&nbsp;2016, Mr.&nbsp;Bilbrey and Ms.&nbsp;Buck had attained age 55 with five years of service and therefore were fully vested in their respective DB SERP benefits. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">69 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The combination of the pension and DB&nbsp;SERP plans was designed to provide a benefit upon retirement at or
after reaching age 60 based on a joint and survivor annuity equal to 55% of final average compensation for an executive with 15 or more years of service (reduced pro rata for each year of service under 15). Effective January&nbsp;1,&nbsp;2007, the
benefit payable under the DB&nbsp;SERP to an executive who was age 50 or over as of January&nbsp;1,&nbsp;2007, was reduced by 10%, and the benefit payable to an executive who had not attained age 50 as of January&nbsp;1,&nbsp;2007, was reduced by
20%. As a result, the benefit payable to Mr.&nbsp;Bilbrey was reduced by 10% and the benefit payable to Ms.&nbsp;Buck was reduced by 20%. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Under the terms
of the DB SERP, final average compensation is calculated as the sum of (i)&nbsp;the average of the highest three calendar years of base salary paid over the last five years of employment with the Company and (ii)&nbsp;the average of the highest
three OHIP awards, paid or deferred, for the last five years of employment with the Company. The benefit accrued under the DB&nbsp;SERP is payable upon retirement (subject to the provisions of Section&nbsp;409A of the IRC) as a lump sum or a life
annuity with 50% benefit continuation to the participant&#146;s surviving spouse, or payment may be deferred in accordance with the provisions of the Company&#146;s Deferred Compensation Plan. The lump sum is equal to the actuarial present value of
the joint and survivor pension earned, reduced by the lump sum value of the benefits to be paid under the pension plan and the value of the executive&#146;s Social Security benefits. If the executive terminates employment after age 55 but before age
60, the benefit is reduced for early retirement at a rate of 5%&nbsp;per year for the period until the executive would have turned 60. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">On
November&nbsp;16, 2015, the Company and Mr.&nbsp;Bilbrey entered into an amendment to his existing employment agreement, the effect of which was to increase, from five to ten years, the duration of the look-back period for selecting the highest
three years of base salary and annual incentive payment used to calculate Mr.&nbsp;Bilbrey&#146;s final average compensation for determining his benefit under the DB SERP. The amendment also established the interest rate to be applied to the
calculation of amounts payable to Mr.&nbsp;Bilbrey under the DB SERP as the rate equal to the Lump Sum Interest Rate (as defined in the DB SERP) as of October&nbsp;31, 2015. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The following table and explanatory footnote provide information regarding the present value of benefits accrued under the pension plan and the DB&nbsp;SERP,
as applicable, for each NEO as of December&nbsp;31,&nbsp;2016. The amounts shown for the DB&nbsp;SERP reflect the reduction for the present value of the benefits under the pension plan and Social Security benefits. </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-TOP:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #999999; padding-left:8pt"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff"><B><FONT COLOR="#ffffff">Name</FONT></B></FONT></TD>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #999999"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff"><B><FONT COLOR="#ffffff">Plan&nbsp;Name&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></B></FONT></TD>

<P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:7.5pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Ms.&nbsp;Turner</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD NOWRAP VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD NOWRAP VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b" ALIGN="right">&#151;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD NOWRAP VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b; padding-right:2pt">&nbsp;</TD></TR>
</TABLE></DIV> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B><A NAME="toc348571_39"></A>2016 <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Non-Qualified</FONT> Deferred Compensation Table
</B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Our NEOs are eligible to participate in the Company&#146;s Deferred Compensation Plan. The Deferred Compensation Plan is a <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-qualified,</FONT> <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-funded</FONT> plan that permits participants to defer compensation that would otherwise be paid to them currently. The Deferred Compensation Plan is intended to
secure the goodwill and loyalty of participants by enabling them to defer compensation when the participants deem it beneficial to do so and by providing a vehicle for the Company to make, on a <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-qualified</FONT>
basis, contributions that could not be made on the participants&#146; behalf to the 401(k) plan. The Company credits the Deferred Compensation Plan with a specified percentage of compensation for NEOs participating in the <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-qualified</FONT> DC&nbsp;SERP. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Our NEOs may elect to defer payments to be received from the DB&nbsp;SERP, DC&nbsp;SERP,
OHIP, PSU and RSU awards, but not stock options or base salary. Amounts deferred are fully vested and are credited to the individual&#146;s account under the Deferred Compensation Plan. Participants elect to receive payment at termination of
employment or some other future date. DB&nbsp;SERP payments designated for deferral into the Deferred Compensation Plan are not credited as earned but are credited in full upon the participant&#146;s retirement. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Payments are distributed in a lump sum or in annual installments for up to 15 years. All amounts are payable in a lump sum following a Change in Control (as
such terms is defined in the EICP). All elections and payments under the Deferred Compensation Plan are subject to compliance with Section&nbsp;409A of the IRC, which may limit elections and require a delay in payment of benefits in certain
circumstances. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">While deferred, amounts are credited with notional earnings as if they were invested by the participant in one or more investment options
offered by the Deferred Compensation Plan. The investment options under the Deferred Compensation Plan consist of investment in a deferred common stock unit account that we value according to the performance of our Common Stock (for awards paid in
stock) or in mutual funds or other investments available to participants in our 401(k) plan (for awards paid in cash). The participants&#146; accounts under the Deferred Compensation Plan fluctuate daily, depending upon performance of the investment
options elected. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">71 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Effective January&nbsp;1,&nbsp;2007, we began crediting the deferred compensation accounts of all employees,
including the NEOs, with the amount of employer matching contributions that exceed the limits established by the IRS for contribution to the 401(k) plan. These amounts are credited in the first quarter of the year after they are earned. As shown in
the footnotes to the 2016 Summary Compensation Table, these amounts are designated as &#147;Supplemental 401(k) Match&#148; and are included as &#147;All Other Compensation&#148; in the year earned. These amounts also are included in Column&nbsp;(c)
of the 2016 <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Non-Qualified</FONT> Deferred Compensation Table in the year earned. With the exception of Ms.&nbsp;Little, all of the NEOs are fully vested in the Supplemental 401(k) Match credits presented and will be
paid at a future date or at termination of employment, as elected by the executive subject to the provisions of Section&nbsp;409A of the IRC. Ms.&nbsp;Little will vest in this benefit upon completion of two years of employment. If vested, she will
receive payment for this benefit at termination of employment subject to the provisions of Section&nbsp;409A of the IRC. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Effective
January&nbsp;1,&nbsp;2007, we began crediting the deferred compensation accounts of all employees hired on or after January&nbsp;1,&nbsp;2007, including eligible NEOs, with the amount of Core Retirement Contributions that exceed the limits
established by the IRS for contribution to the 401(k) plan. These amounts are credited in the first quarter of the year after they are earned. As shown in the footnotes to the 2016 Summary Compensation Table, these amounts are designated as
&#147;Supplemental Core Retirement Contribution&#148; and are included as &#147;All Other Compensation&#148; in the year earned. These amounts also are included in Column&nbsp;(c) of the 2016 <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Non-Qualified</FONT>
Deferred Compensation Table in the year earned. Mmes. Little and Turner and Mr.&nbsp;O&#146;Day are eligible for a Supplemental CRC credit for 2016. Ms.&nbsp;Turner and Mr.&nbsp;O&#146;Day are fully vested in this benefit and will receive payment at
termination of employment subject to the provisions of Section&nbsp;409A of the IRC. Ms.&nbsp;Little will vest in this benefit upon completion of two years of employment. If vested, she will receive payment for this benefit at termination of
employment subject to the provisions of Section&nbsp;409A of the IRC. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Mmes. Little and Turner and Mr.&nbsp;O&#146;Day are also eligible to participate in
our DC&nbsp;SERP, a part of the Deferred Compensation Plan. The DC&nbsp;SERP provides annual allocations to the Deferred Compensation Plan equal to a percentage of compensation determined by the Compensation Committee in its sole discretion. In
order to receive the annual DC&nbsp;SERP allocation, an executive must (i)&nbsp;defer into the 401(k) plan the maximum amount allowed by the Company or the IRS and (ii)&nbsp;be employed on the last day of the plan year, unless the executive
terminates employment after age 55 and completion of five years of continuous employment preceding termination, dies or becomes disabled. After completing five years of service with the Company, an executive is vested in 10% increments based on his
or her age. An executive age&nbsp;46 with five years of service is 10% vested and an executive age 55 with five years of service is 100% vested. The annual DC&nbsp;SERP allocation for Mmes. Little and Turner and Mr.&nbsp;O&#146;Day is equal to 12.5%
of base salary and OHIP award for the calendar year, whether paid or deferred. Mr.&nbsp;O&#146;Day is 100% vested in his DC&nbsp;SERP benefit, while Mmes. Little and Turner are 0% vested because they have not yet completed five years of continuous
employment with the Company. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">72 </P>

<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B><A NAME="toc348571_40"></A>Potential Payments upon Termination or Change in Control </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">We maintain plans covering our NEOs that will require us to provide incremental compensation in the event of termination of employment or a Change in Control
(as such term is defined in the applicable governing document), provided certain conditions are met. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The following narrative takes each termination of
employment situation &#150; voluntary resignation, termination for Cause, death, disability, retirement, termination without Cause, and resignation for Good Reason &#150; and a Change in Control of the Company, and describes the additional amounts,
if any, that the Company would pay or provide to the NEOs, or their beneficiaries, as a result. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">73 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The narrative below and the amounts shown reflect certain assumptions we have made in accordance with SEC rules.
We have assumed that the termination of employment or Change in Control occurred on December&nbsp;31, 2016, and that the value of a share of our Common Stock on that day was $103.43, the closing price on the NYSE on December&nbsp;30,&nbsp;2016, the
last trading day of 2016. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">In addition, in keeping with SEC rules, the following narrative and amounts do not include payments and benefits which are not
enhanced by a qualifying termination of employment or Change in Control. These payments and benefits are referred to as &#147;vested benefits&#148; and include: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Vested benefits accrued under the 401(k) and pension plans; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Accrued vacation pay, health plan continuation and other similar amounts payable when employment terminates under programs generally applicable to the Company&#146;s salaried employees; </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Vested Supplemental 401(k) Match and Supplemental CRC provided to the NEOs on the same basis as all other employees eligible for Supplemental 401(k) Match and Supplemental CRC; </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Vested benefits accrued under the DB&nbsp;SERP and account balances held under the Deferred Compensation Plan as previously described in the sections entitled &#147;2016 Pension Benefits Table&#148; and &#147;2016 <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Non-Qualified</FONT> Deferred Compensation Table&#148;; and </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Stock options which have vested and become exercisable prior to termination of employment or Change in Control. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><I>Voluntary Resignation (other than a Resignation for Good Reason) </I></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">We are not obligated to pay amounts over and above vested benefits to a NEO who voluntarily resigns. Vested stock options may not be exercised after the
NEO&#146;s resignation date unless the executive meets retirement eligibility requirements (separation after attainment of age 55 with at least five years of continuous service). </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><I>Termination for Cause </I></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">If we terminate a NEO&#146;s
employment for Cause, we are not obligated to pay the executive any amounts over and above vested benefits. The NEO&#146;s right to exercise vested stock options expires upon termination for Cause, and amounts otherwise payable under the
DB&nbsp;SERP are subject to forfeiture at the Company&#146;s discretion. In general, a termination will be for Cause if the executive has been convicted of a felony or has engaged in gross negligence or willful misconduct in the performance of
duties, material dishonesty or a material violation of Company policies, including our Code of Ethical Business Conduct, or bad faith actions in the performance of duties not in the best interests of the Company. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><I>Death or Disability </I></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">If a NEO dies prior to meeting the
vesting requirements under the DB SERP, no benefits are paid. As of December&nbsp;31, 2016, Mr.&nbsp;Bilbrey and Ms.&nbsp;Buck were fully vested in their respective DB&nbsp;SERP benefits and their respective estates would therefore be entitled to a
payout of such benefits in the event of their death. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">74 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">In the event of termination due to disability, long-term disability (&#147;LTD&#148;) benefits are generally
payable until age 65, but may extend for longer if disability benefits begin after age 60, and are offset by other benefits such as Social Security. The maximum amount of the monthly LTD payments from all sources, assuming LTD began on
December&nbsp;31,&nbsp;2016, is set forth in the table below: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">

<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><I>Treatment of Stock Options upon Retirement, Death or Disability </I></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">In the event of retirement, death or disability, vested stock options remain exercisable for a period of three or five years, not to exceed the option
expiration date. The exercise period is based upon the terms and conditions of the individual grant. Retirement is defined as separation after attainment of age 55 with at least five years of continuous service. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Options that are not vested at the time of retirement, death or disability will generally vest in full (subject to the exception described in the following
sentence) and the options will remain exercisable for three or five years following termination, depending on the terms and conditions of the grant. Options granted in the year of retirement are prorated based upon the number of full calendar months
worked in that year. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">75 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The following table provides the number of unvested stock options as of December&nbsp;31,&nbsp;2016, that would
have become vested and remained exercisable during the three-year or five-year periods following death or disability, or retirement if applicable, on December&nbsp;31,&nbsp;2016, and the value of those options based on the excess of the fair market
value of our Common Stock on December&nbsp;30, 2016, the last trading day of 2016, over the applicable option exercise price. As of December&nbsp;31,&nbsp;2016, Messrs.&nbsp;Bilbrey, O&#146;Day and Ms.&nbsp;Buck were considered retirement eligible
based on the provisions of all outstanding option awards. Because Mmes.&nbsp;Little and Turner were not considered retirement eligible as of December&nbsp;31,&nbsp;2016, they would forfeit 53,908 stock options and 76,843 stock options, respectively,
upon voluntary separation. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(1)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Represents the total number of unvested options as of December&nbsp;31, 2016. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Reflects the difference between $103.43 the closing price for our Common Stock on the NYSE on December&nbsp;30, 2016, the last trading day of 2016, and the exercise price for each option. Options for which the exercise
price exceeds $103.43 are not included in the calculations. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><I>Treatment of RSUs upon Retirement, Death or Disability </I></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Upon retirement, any unvested RSUs are forfeited. Unvested RSUs will vest in full upon death or disability. </P>

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><I>Treatment of PSUs upon Retirement, Death or Disability </I></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">In the event of retirement, death or disability, any unvested contingent PSUs are prorated based on the number of full or partial months worked in each of the
open PSU cycles. Any remaining unvested contingent PSUs not prorated are forfeited. The following table provides the total number of contingent PSUs each NEO would be entitled to if the executive&#146;s employment ended on December&nbsp;31, 2016 due
to death or disability, or retirement if applicable. As of December&nbsp;31, 2016, Messrs. Bilbrey and O&#146;Day and Ms.&nbsp;Buck were considered retirement eligible based on the provisions of all open PSU cycles. Because Mmes. Little and Turner
were not considered retirement eligible as of December&nbsp;31, 2016, they would forfeit all of their contingent PSUs upon voluntary separation. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Based on the closing price of $103.43 for our Common Stock on the NYSE on December&nbsp;30, 2016, the last trading day of 2016. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><I>Termination without Cause; Resignation for Good Reason </I></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Under Mr.&nbsp;Bilbrey&#146;s employment agreement and the EBPP&nbsp;3A, as applicable, we have agreed to pay severance benefits if we terminate a NEO&#146;s
active employment without Cause or if the NEO resigns from active employment for Good Reason, in each case as defined in the applicable document. Severance benefits consist of a lump sum payment calculated as a multiple of base salary and target
OHIP as well as continuation of health and welfare benefits for a set period of time, as shown in the table below. Additionally, all NEOs would be entitled to receive a pro rata payment of the OHIP award, if any, earned for the year in which
termination occurs. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">77 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">If a NEO has not met retirement eligibility requirements and his or her employment is terminated for reasons
other than for Cause, or if the NEO terminates for Good Reason, he or she will be eligible to exercise all vested stock options and a prorated portion of his or her unvested stock options held on the date of separation from service for a period of
120 days following separation. If the NEO is age 55 or older with five or more years of continuous service and his or her employment is terminated for reasons other than for Cause, or if the NEO terminates for Good Reason, the NEO will be entitled
to exercise any vested stock options until the earlier of three or five years (based on the provisions of the individual grant) from the date of termination or the expiration of the options. In addition, if a NEO&#146;s employment is terminated for
reasons other than for Cause, or if the NEO terminates for Good Reason, the NEO will vest in a prorated portion of any unvested RSUs held on the date of separation from service. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The following table provides the incremental amounts that would have been payable to each NEO had his or her employment terminated on
December&nbsp;31,&nbsp;2016, under circumstances entitling the NEO to severance benefits as described above: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

Fiscal-Year End Table. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><I>Change in Control </I></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The
EBPP&nbsp;3A provides for the vesting and payment of the following benefits to each of the NEOs upon a Change in Control: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">An OHIP payment for the year in which the Change in Control occurs, calculated as the greater of target or the estimated payment based on actual performance through the date of the Change in Control; </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">To the extent not vested, full vesting of benefits accrued under the DB&nbsp;SERP and the Deferred Compensation Plan; and </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">To the extent not vested, full vesting of benefits under the 401(k) and pension plans. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Under our EICP, awards
are continued as qualifying replacement awards after a Change in Control, and therefore, no accelerated vesting or payment will occur for such awards because of the Change in Control. In the event of termination of employment within two years
following the Change in Control for any reason other than termination for Cause or resignation without Good Reason, the replacement awards will vest and become payable as described below. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">78 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

would have vested and become payable on December&nbsp;31,&nbsp;2016, if a Change in Control occurred on that date. All unvested awards would continue as qualifying replacement awards, and therefore are not included in the table below: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">The amount of the OHIP award earned for 2016 was greater than target. Therefore no incremental amount attributable to that program would have been payable upon a Change in Control. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:7.5pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(2)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Reflects the full vesting value of DB SERP benefits and more favorable early retirement discount factors as provided under the EBPP 3A. Mr.&nbsp;Bilbrey is fully vested in his unreduced DB SERP benefit so no additional
benefit is applicable. Ms.&nbsp;Buck is fully vested in her DB SERP benefit so the amount includes the value of more favorable early retirement discount factors. For Ms.&nbsp;Little, the amount includes the vesting of her DC SERP benefit, 401(k),
Supplemental Match, CRC and Supplemental CRC. Mr.&nbsp;O&#146;Day is fully vested in his DC SERP benefit so no additional benefit is applicable. For Ms.&nbsp;Turner, the amount includes the vesting of her DC SERP benefit. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:7.5pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(3)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">For any given executive, the total payments made in the event of termination after a Change in Control would be reduced to the &#147;safe harbor&#148; limit under IRC Section 280G if such reduction would result in a
greater <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">after-tax</FONT> benefit for the executive. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><I>Termination without Cause or Resignation for Good
Reason after Change in Control </I></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">If a NEO&#146;s employment is terminated by the Company without Cause or by the NEO for Good Reason within two years
after a Change in Control, we pay severance benefits under the EBPP 3A to assist the NEO in transitioning to new employment. These severance benefits as of December&nbsp;31,&nbsp;2016, consist of: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">A lump sum cash payment equal to two (or, if less, the number of full and fractional years from the date of termination to the executive&#146;s 65<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">th</SUP> birthday, but not
less than one) times: </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="9%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL"><SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#161;</FONT></SUP>&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top"></SUP>The executive&#146;s base salary; and </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="9%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL"><SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#161;</FONT></SUP>&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top"></SUP>The highest OHIP award payment paid or payable during the three years preceding the year of the Change in Control (but not less than the OHIP target award for the
year of the termination); </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">For replacement PSU awards, full vesting of PSUs for the performance cycle ending in the year of the Change in Control. The cash payment will be based upon the greater of target or actual performance through the date of
the Change in Control, with each PSU valued at the highest closing price for our Common Stock during the 60 days prior to the Change in Control; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">For replacement PSU awards, full vesting of outstanding PSUs at target that are in the second year of the performance cycle and prorated vesting of outstanding PSUs at target that are in the first year of the
performance cycle at the time of the Change in Control; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">For replacement stock options and RSU awards (including accrued cash credits equivalent to dividends that would have been earned had the executive held Common Stock instead of RSUs), full vesting of all unvested stock
options and RSUs; </TD></TR></TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">79 </P>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Continuation of medical, dental, vision and life benefits for 24 months (or, if less, the number of months until the executive attains age 65, but not less than 12 months), or payment of the value of such benefits if
continuation is not permitted under the terms of the applicable plan; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

number of full and fractional years from the date of termination to the executive&#146;s 65<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">th</SUP> birthday, but not less than one). IRS limitations imposed on the 401(k) and pension plans will not
apply for this purpose; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4%; font-size:7.5pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Because Messrs. Bilbrey and O&#146;Day and Ms.&nbsp;Buck were retirement eligible as of
December&nbsp;31, 2016, as of that date they had already vested in a portion of the PSU awards for the performance cycles ending December&nbsp;31, 2017 and December&nbsp;31, 2018. Accordingly, with respect to these NEOs, the amount for the
performance cycle ending December&nbsp;31, 2017, reflects only (i)&nbsp;an incremental payment of the portion of the PSU award that would vest upon termination following a Change in Control (<I>i.e.</I> 1/3 of the total award) and (ii)&nbsp;an
incremental benefit equal to the difference between a value per PSU of $104.44 the highest closing price of our Common Stock on the NYSE during the last 60 days of 2016, and a value per PSU of $103.43 the closing price of our Common Stock on the
NYSE on December&nbsp;30, 2016, the last trading day of 2016, while the amount for the performance cycle ending December&nbsp;31, 2018, reflects only an incremental benefit equal to the difference between a value per PSU of $104.44 and a value per
PSU of $103.43. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:7.5pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(2)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Reflects the value of unvested options that would vest upon the executive&#146;s employment termination following a Change in Control based on the excess, if any, of the value of our Common Stock of $103.43 on
December&nbsp;30, 2016, the last trading day of 2016, over the exercise price for the options. Information regarding unvested options as of December&nbsp;31, 2016 can be found in the Outstanding Equity Awards at 2016 Fiscal-Year End Table.
</TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:7.5pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

of DC SERP, CRC, Supplemental CRC, 401(k) Match and Supplemental 401(k) Match that would have been paid had they remained employees for 24 months after their termination. For Mr.&nbsp;O&#146;Day, the value reflects the amounts of DC SERP, CRC,
Supplemental CRC, 401(k) Match and Supplemental 401(k) Match that would have been paid had he remained an employee for 12 months after his termination. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:13.5pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><B><A NAME="toc348571_41"></A>PROPOSAL NO. 3 &#150; ADVISE ON NAMED
EXECUTIVE </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:13.5pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><B>OFFICER COMPENSATION </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:12pt" ALIGN="center">


<TR>
<TD></TD>
<TD></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="4%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="90%"></TD></TR>


<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:12pt">
<TD VALIGN="middle" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-TOP:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b; padding-left:8pt"><FONT STYLE="font-size:40pt">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b" ALIGN="right"><FONT STYLE="font-size:40pt">&#10003;</FONT></TD>
<TD NOWRAP VALIGN="middle" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b"><FONT STYLE="font-size:40pt">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#3f000b" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b; padding-right:2pt" BGCOLOR="#3f000b">
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff">The Board of Directors unanimously recommends that stockholders</FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff">vote <B>FOR</B> approval, on a
<FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-binding</FONT> advisory basis, of the compensation</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><FONT
 COLOR="#ffffff">of the Company&#146;s named executive officers</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt" align="left">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">In accordance with the Dodd-Frank Wall Street Reform and Consumer Protection Act and related SEC rules, and as required under
Section&nbsp;14A of the Exchange Act, we are providing stockholders an opportunity to conduct an advisory vote regarding the compensation of our NEOs as disclosed in this Proxy Statement. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Prior to submitting your vote, we encourage you to read our Compensation Discussion&nbsp;&amp; Analysis and the accompanying executive compensation tables for
details about our executive compensation program, including information about the 2016 compensation of our NEOs. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">As discussed in more detail in the
Compensation Discussion&nbsp;&amp; Analysis, we believe our executive compensation program is competitive and governed by <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">pay-for-performance</FONT></FONT> principles. We emphasize
compensation opportunities that reward results. Our stock ownership requirements and use of stock-based incentives reinforce the alignment of the interests of our executives with those of our long-term stockholders. In doing so, our executive
compensation program supports our strategic objectives and mission. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Accordingly, we ask you to approve the following resolution at the Annual Meeting:
</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#147;RESOLVED, that the stockholders of The Hershey Company approve, on an advisory basis, the compensation paid to the Company&#146;s
named executive officers, as disclosed in the Proxy Statement for the 2017 Annual Meeting of Stockholders pursuant to the SEC&#146;s compensation disclosure rules, including the Compensation Discussion&nbsp;&amp; Analysis, the Executive Compensation
Tables and the related narrative discussion.&#148; </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Because your vote is advisory, it will not be binding upon the Board. However, as noted in the
Compensation Discussion&nbsp;&amp; Analysis, the Compensation Committee and the Board will, as deemed appropriate, take into account the outcome of the vote when considering future decisions affecting executive compensation. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The affirmative vote of the holders of at least a majority of the shares of Common Stock and Class&nbsp;B Common Stock (voting together as a class) represented
at the Annual Meeting, in person or by proxy, is required to approve this proposal. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">82 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:13.5pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#3f000b"><B><A NAME="toc348571_42"></A>PROPOSAL NO. 4 &#150; ADVISE ON FREQUENCY OF
FUTURE ADVISORY VOTES ON NAMED EXECUTIVE OFFICER COMPENSATION </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:12pt" ALIGN="center">


<TR>
<TD></TD>
<TD></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="90%"></TD></TR>


<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:12pt">
<TD VALIGN="middle" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-TOP:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b; padding-left:8pt"><FONT STYLE="font-size:40pt">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b" ALIGN="right"><FONT STYLE="font-size:40pt">&#10003;</FONT></TD>
<TD NOWRAP VALIGN="middle" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b"><FONT STYLE="font-size:40pt">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#3f000b" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #3f000b; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #3f000b; padding-right:2pt" BGCOLOR="#3f000b">
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff">The Board of Directors unanimously recommends that stockholders</FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff">vote to hold future advisory votes on named executive officer
compensation</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff">every <B>1 YEAR</B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt" align="left">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">In accordance with the Dodd-Frank Wall Street Reform and Consumer Protection Act and related SEC rules, and as required under
Section&nbsp;14A of the Exchange Act, we are providing stockholders an opportunity to conduct an advisory vote regarding the frequency with which future advisory votes on the compensation of our NEOs should be held. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">At our 2011 Annual Meeting of Stockholders, a majority of stockholders indicated a preference for holding advisory votes on NEO compensation every year, and we
have conducted such an annual vote since that time. Under Section 14A of the Exchange Act, every six years we are required to provide stockholders an opportunity to again advise on the frequency with which future votes on NEO compensation should be
held. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">After careful consideration, the Board has determined that continuing to conduct an advisory vote on NEO compensation each year remains the most
appropriate policy at this time. The Board believes such an annual vote best enables stockholders to timely express their views on the Company&#146;s executive compensation program and policies and assists the Board and the Compensation Committee in
determining current stockholder sentiment. Additionally, conducting an annual advisory vote on NEO compensation is consistent with our practice of regularly seeking input from stockholders on corporate governance matters. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">You are not being asked to vote &#147;for&#148; or &#147;against&#148; this proposal. Instead, this proposal asks stockholders to inform us how often we should
conduct an advisory vote on the compensation of our NEOs. You may cast your vote by choosing the option of every 1, 2 or 3 years, or abstaining, in response to the following resolution: </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#147;RESOLVED, that the option of every 1 year, 2 years or 3 years that receives the highest number of votes cast for this resolution will be
determined to be the preferred frequency with which the Company is to hold future advisory votes on named executive officer compensation, as disclosed in the Company&#146;s annual proxy statement pursuant to the SEC&#146;s compensation disclosure
rules, including the Compensation Discussion&nbsp;&amp; Analysis, the Executive Compensation Tables and the related narrative discussion.&#148; </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The
frequency that receives the greatest number of votes from the holders of our Common Stock and Class&nbsp;B Common Stock voting together will be deemed to be stockholders&#146; preferred frequency for conducting future advisory votes on NEO
compensation. Because your vote is advisory, it will not be binding upon the Board. However, the Board will, as it deems appropriate, take into account the outcome of the vote when determining how often the Company will conduct advisory votes on NEO
compensation in future years. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">83 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><B><A NAME="toc348571_43"></A>SECTION 16(a) BENEFICIAL OWNERSHIP </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><B>REPORTING COMPLIANCE </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Section&nbsp;16(a) of
the Exchange Act requires our directors and executive officers, as well as any person who is the beneficial owner of more than 10% of our outstanding Common Stock, to file reports with the SEC and NYSE showing their ownership and changes in
ownership of the Company&#146;s securities. Copies of these reports also must be furnished to us. Based on an examination of these reports and on written representations provided to us, it is our opinion that all reports for 2016 were timely filed,
except for a Form 4 filed by Thomas J. Ridge on April&nbsp;21, 2016 reporting the disposition of shares on March&nbsp;
9, 2016. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:24pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><B><A NAME="toc348571_44"></A>CERTAIN TRANSACTIONS AND RELATIONSHIPS </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Item&nbsp;404 of SEC Regulation <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">S-K</FONT> requires that we disclose any transaction or series of similar transactions, or any
currently proposed transaction(s), in which (i)&nbsp;the Company was or is to be a participant, (ii)&nbsp;the amount involved exceeds $120,000 and (iii)&nbsp;any of the following persons had or will have a direct or indirect material interest: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
